A collision of three buses in the Cape Town CBD has left 32 people injured on Tuesday.The accident occurred at the corners of Heerengracht and Hertzog Boulevard in Cape Town.According to ER24, paramedics found the three buses parked on the side of the road with the occupants spread across the scene.There are no serious or fatal injuries reported on the scene and patients have been sent to various hospitals for further treatment.Traffic is heavily affected due to the collision. &nbsp; ADVISORY. Due to an accident at Civic Centre Station most services making use of the station may experience delays. &mdash; MyCiTi Bus (@MyCiTiBus) November 8, 2016 ADVISORY. Due to an accident at Civic Centre Station most services making use of the station may experience delays.&mdash; MyCiTi Bus (@MyCiTiBus) November 8, 2016Local authorities will be conducting an investigation into the cause of the collision. &nbsp; Mass casualty incident in the CPT CBD on the corners of Heerengracht and Hertzog boulevard involving 3 busses. Please avoid the area. &mdash; ER24 EMS (Pty) Ltd. (@ER24EMS) November 8, 2016 Mass casualty incident in the CPT CBD on the corners of Heerengracht and Hertzog boulevard involving 3 busses. Please avoid the area.&mdash; ER24 EMS (Pty) Ltd. (@ER24EMS) November 8, 2016&nbsp; [UPDATE] &#8211; A total of 32 patients were treated and transported from the bus collision in CPT CBD. @ewnupdates @eNCA @KFMza @_ArriveAlive &mdash; ER24 EMS (Pty) Ltd. (@ER24EMS) November 8, 2016 [UPDATE] &#8211; A total of 32 patients were treated and transported from the bus collision in CPT CBD. @ewnupdates @eNCA @KFMza @_ArriveAlive&mdash; ER24 EMS (Pty) Ltd. (@ER24EMS) November 8, 2016-Aviwe Maxheke